Colombia Stock Movers: Exito, Argos, ETB, Grupo Sura, Rubiales

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-03-17T21:10:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/colombia-stock-movers-ecopetrol-exito-argos-grupo-sura-rise.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index gained 3.8 percent to 14,407.42, while the
Colcap Index climbed 4.3 percent to 1,708.98.  Financial and retail stocks rose on prospects  Colombia ’s
investment-grade designation yesterday will lower borrowing
costs, boosting credit growth.    Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  , Colombia’s biggest publicly-
traded retailer, jumped 5.1 percent to 26,300 pesos, a record.    Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA (GRUPOSUR)  , the
parent company of Colombia’s largest bank, climbed 5.8 percent
to 37,100 pesos.    Cementos Argos SA (CEMARGOS)  , Colombia’s biggest cement
maker, rose 6 percent to 10,620 pesos, the biggest increase
since October 2008. Colombia’s boost to investment grade by  Standard & Poor’s  yesterday suggests the economy can grow 6
percent, Finance Minister Juan Carlos Echeverry told  Caracol
Radio .    Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota (ETB)  SA, the
telecommunications provider serving Colombia’s capital, rose 5.3
percent to 655 pesos. State-controlled companies climbed after
the nation’s foreign debt rating was upgraded to BBB- by S&P.
Isagen SA (ISAGEN CB), a state-controlled power producer,
increased 6.1 percent to 2,420 pesos.    Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PREC)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, surged 6.6
percent to 53,300 pesos. Crude  oil prices  climbed the most in
three weeks on concern that unrest in North Africa and the
Middle East will spread, reducing shipments from the region.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
